The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | 3 arrested for book on riots
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     3 arrested for book on riots
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Dec. 8: Three persons, including the owner of a press, were forwarded to court for allegedly printing and circulating a provocative book on communal violence in Kandhamal.         
	The trio  press owner Lenin Kumar, workers Rabi Jena and Dhananjaya Lenka  were later remanded in judicial custody as their bail pleas had been rejected by the court of sub-divisional judicial magistrate.        
	The book, Dharma Nare Kandhamalare Raktara Banya (Bloodshed in Kandhamal in the Name of Religion), contained provocative and inciting contents, police said.        
	Copies of the hugely circulated book were also seized.         
	About 700 copies of the book have been seized from the press, said deputy commissioner of police Himanshu Lal, adding that the press had been sealed.        
	Lenin was arrested under Sections 293(a) and 163(a) of the IPC. He also edits a periodical, Nishan. The police raided the press after Maoist posters were found at several places here in the past week.                                                                                                                                                                          
